    "summary": "GNOME GLib before 2.65.3 has an integer overflow, that might lead to an out-of-bounds write, in...",
    "details": "GNOME GLib before 2.65.3 has an integer overflow, that might lead to an out-of-bounds write, in `g_option_group_add_entries`. NOTE: the vendor's position is \"Realistically this is not a security issue. The standard pattern is for callers to provide a static list of option entries in a fixed number of calls to `g_option_group_add_entries()`.\" The researcher states that this pattern is undocumented",
